    "body": "### Problem\n\nTrying to open a file with a UNC path: `$ nvim \\\\?\\C:\\some-file.txt` gives this message immediatlely: `E303: Unable to open swap file for \"\\\\?\\C:\\some-file.txt\", recovery impossible`. The usual version of this path would be `C:\\some-file.txt` and that works just fine.\r\n\r\nI also noticed this same issue with undofile when using with `jj commit` but I don't have an immediate reproducing example.\r\n\r\n[Microsoft docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/fileio/naming-a-file#fully-qualified-vs-relative-paths)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\nnvim \\\\?\\C:\\some-file.txt\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expected it to work without emitting warnings and to use the same swap & undo files as when it's opened with a relative path or the traditional `C:\\some-file.txt`.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-313+gfc9b70826\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly zip",
